## Update — VOD 2813242741 result + a real bug fixed (still same session)

The catch-up run on `2813242741` finished: **both** `audioTransient`
(yt-dlp exit 1 at 100% of a 270MB download) and `motion` (hit its 30-min
timeout) failed. 0 highlights, 0 clips. Looks like a network/download
reliability issue on this machine at the time, not a config bug — both
failures were at the download step.

**Bug found and fixed:** `src/pipeline.js`'s `runPipeline` was marking a
VOD as "processed" even when every detector failed (per-detector failures
are caught inside `runDetectors` and returned as data, not thrown, so
`processVod` never threw and the "skip marking processed" branch never
triggered). `2813242741` got silently marked done with zero clips — nothing
would have ever retried it. Fixed: `processVod` now also returns
`detectorsRun`; `runPipeline` treats "all detectors failed" the same as a
thrown `pipelineError` (VOD stays unmarked, Discord gets a `FAILED`
summary). Logged in `ERRORS.md` with full detail. Tests still pass (same
2 pre-existing `env.test.js` failures, nothing new broken).

