## RESOLVED 2026-07-06 (commits 5487e20, 0505aeb) — detection fixed & verified

The reprocess above came back "complete, 0 highlights" — investigated and
fixed. Root causes:
1. `yt-dlp -o -` stages HLS fragments as `--FragN` CWD temp files; a Windows
   read-back race killed the 270MB audio download at 79% (run 2) and 99.8%
   (run 1). Fixed: new `src/lib/streamUrl.js` resolves the m3u8 via
   `yt-dlp -g`; ffmpeg reads HLS directly. ~21x realtime now (audio pass 69s).
2. `motion` NEVER worked on Windows: the absolute temp path in
   `metadata=print:file=` broke the filtergraph parse instantly; the pipe's
   settle logic masked it as the 30-min "timeout". Fixed: spawn ffmpeg with
   cwd = temp dir + bare relative filename. Full 3h VOD scans in ~8 min.
3. `reprocess-vod.js` reported all-detectors-failed as "complete" — now
   reports FAILED (exit 1) and posts live per-detector progress pings.
Also done: audio wall-clock timeout added (`detector.audioTimeoutMs`) —
closes the "known remaining gap" flagged above.

**Verified live:** reprocess 2813242741 → 20 highlights, 20 Twitch clips
published, 20 TikTok drafts, 0 failures. Standalone full-VOD motion run:
238 scene events → 20 highlights in 470s (detection only, not published).

